{"tid":2449231,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"緬甸手足 出聲明,屌柒 中國政府 更改 香港選舉方法","createTime":"2021-03-16T13:28:43.000Z","updateTime":"2021-03-17T12:06:38.000Z","uid":54623,"like":148,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":58,"replies":[{"pid":"ae14e8c57b5076119d27880939ab5bd83f98f8ab","tid":2449231,"uid":54623,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-16T13:28:43.000Z","msg":"請去twitter留言,多謝緬甸手足.&nbsp;同幫推<br />\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/EithinzarMM/status/1371767306045566981\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FEithinzarMM%2Fstatus%2F1371767306045566981&d=JW7tglSI9GVP0ZLjrScixRjXlokmAnOoGQHL1SEg040%3D&h=94ae11c6\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FEithinzarMM%2Fstatus%2F1371767306045566981&h=612773ad\" target=\"_blank\">https://twitter.com/EithinzarMM/status/1371767306045566981</a><br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/gz2SACR.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2Fgz2SACR.jpg&h=a42f3fca&s={SIZE}\" /> <br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/s8AwRbc.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2Fs8AwRbc.jpg&h=7305f8e4&s={SIZE}\" /> <br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/LRZxADf.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FLRZxADf.jpg&h=210bc64c&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n16th March 2021 <br />\nOur dear Asian activists, <br />\nToday in 2021, the spring revolution is to overthrow the oppressive governments and to build democracy that ensures our freedom, to build an economy that benefits us, and to build a justice system that protects our rights in our respective nations. <br />\n<br />\nOur governments, for decades, have wilfully neglected people's interests that contradicts their purpose of existence and often times they confide in the Big Brother Beijing.<br />\n<br />\n We condemn the recent changes in electoral procedures that silent the voice of the people of Hong Kong, punishing political prisoners and activists, detaining lawyers and human right activists, the national security law to restrict the right to freedom of movement by legislating immigration laws that prohibits Hong Kong residents to leave the city. We the Burmese people stand together with brothers and sisters from Hong Kong who are fighting against these perverse decisions made by Hong Kong government that outright enables the Chinese hegemony over Hong Kong. <br />\n<br />\nAlthough the Myanmar military aka Terrorist Tatmadaw does not have a direct relations with China as Hong Kong government has, the influence of the Chinese government over the Terrorist military is plain as day. On 14th March, the Chinese Embassy in Myanmar published a post calling for security of Chinese workers at the factories that caught fire. They implied that the fire was caused by protesters. That was baseless claim to justify the violence towards civilians. There were live videos on facebook in which the locals are trying to extinguish the fire without the help from fire departments. Myanmar military is known their arsonist tactics where they set fire on properties and blame it on the victims. That was a small incident comparing to the extreme crackdowns across the country. As of now, over 180 people have been shot dead and over 2000 people arrested. While the several injured people are cared under insufficient medical assistance, the Chinese Embassy in Myanmar asked for the terrorist State Administration Council's protection for Chinese factories and workers in Hlaing Thar Yar township where the military killed at least 22 civilians were shot dead, more than 25 civilians were wounded severely. As ironic as it appears, the terrorist SAC announced to take Hlaing Thar Yar and Shwe Pyi Thar townships directly under military control. <br />\n<br />\nAs a result of the statement by Chinese Embassy in Myanmar, direct military rule is in action in the industrial zones of Yangon, Myanmar. It is in deep concern that further exacerbates the plight of local people who are going through difficult times. <br />\n<br />\nSuch actions by the Chinese government towards its neighbouring countries are not acceptable by any means. Therefore we urge the Chinese government to scrutinise current relations with the SAC terrorists. We again ask of the Chinese government to stop endorsing the Burmese dictators. <br />\n<br />\nWe the locals have sole rights to our freedom and our economic advantages belong to us. The power of our nation lies in us."},{"pid":"f4d0a28d773022349365b9a8e5700eb1760ca484","tid":2449231,"uid":5649,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-16T13:29:05.000Z","msg":"推"},{"pid":"e58fe015e7be9ae691f670fb86ff2807702bd10a","tid":2449231,"uid":88743,"like":5,"dislike":1,"score":4,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-16T13:32:55.000Z","msg":"之後格黎我開個PO啲人有咁既反應<br />\n<br />\n<blockquote>人地上街關香港人乜事<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<blockquote>我憑咩撐唔撐（緬甸）<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<blockquote>樓豬係屋企開住冷氣撐<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/touch.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n【公投】一句到尾，連登仔撐唔撐緬甸示威者繼續街頭抗爭？<br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區 <br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/2449137\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/2449137</a>"},{"pid":"aa1cfab1d6ded41970ec56dec6363d281dd183c5","tid":2449231,"uid":3776,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-16T13:37:29.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n屌 好撚感動<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"213605b9138d8152cc980e30709a25777055f629",